definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To connect (two or more things).
( intransitive , Internet , of a web page ) To contain a hyperlink to another page.
examples: My homepage links to my wife's.

definitions.definition: ( transitive , Internet ) To supply (someone) with a hyperlink ; to direct by means of a link.
examples: Haven't you seen his website? I'll link you to it.

definitions.definition: ( transitive , Internet ) To post a hyperlink to.
examples: Stop linking those unfunny comics all the time!

definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To demonstrate a correlation between (two things).
( software compilation ) To combine objects generated by a compiler into a single executable .

definitions.definition: To skip or trip along smartly ; to go quickly.
